quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  70,19,Truly man was created anxious
  70,20,"when evil befalls him, fretful"
  70,21,"and when good befalls him, begrudging"
  70,22,save those who perform prayer
  70,23,who are constant in their prayers
  70,24,and in whose wealth is an acknowledged due
  70,25,for the beggar and the deprived
  70,26,those who affirm the Day of Judgment
  70,27,and who are wary of the punishment of their Lord—
  70,28,truly there is no security from the punishment of their Lord
  70,29,those who guard their private parts
  70,30,"save from their spouses or those whom their right hands possess, for then they are not blameworthy"
  70,31,"but whosoever seeks beyond that, they are the transgressors"
  70,32,those who abide by their trusts and their pact
  70,33,who uphold their testimony
  70,34,and who are mindful of their prayers
  70,35,"those shall be in Gardens, honored"
  70,36,So how is it that those who disbelieve scramble toward thee
  70,37,from the right and from the left in droves
  70,38,Does every man among them desire to be admitted into a Garden of bliss
  70,39,Nay! Truly We created them from that which they know
  70,40,So I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests that We are able
  70,41,"to replace [them] with what is better than them; and none outstrips Us"
  70,42,So leave them to indulge in idle talk and play until they meet the Day that they are promised
  70,43,"a day when they come forth from their graves, hastening as if racing to a goal"
  70,44,"their eyes humbled, abasement shall overcome them. That is the Day they have been promised"
  71,1,"Truly We sent Noah to his people, “Warn thy people before a painful punishment comes upon them.”"
  71,2,"He said, “O my people! I am a clear warner unto you"
  71,3,"that you may worship God, reverence Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"that He may forgive you some of your sins and grant you reprieve until a term appointed. Truly when the term of God comes, it will not be delayed, if you but knew.”"
  71,5,"He said, “My Lord, I have called my people day and night"
  71,6,Yet my calling has not increased them in aught but flight
  71,7,"Truly whenever I call them, that Thou mayest forgive them, they put their fingers in their ears, cover themselves with their garments, persist, and wax most arrogant"
  71,8,Then I called them openly
  71,9,Then I proclaimed to them and confided to them in secret
  71,10,"I said, ‘Seek forgiveness of your Lord! Truly He is Forgiving"
  71,11,He will send the sky upon you with abundant rains
  71,12,"support you with wealth and sons, and make for you gardens and rivers"
  71,13,What ails you that you do not hope for God with dignity
  71,14,seeing that He has created you in stages
  71,15,Have you not considered how God created the seven heavens one upon another
  71,16,and made the moon a light therein and made the sun a lamp
  71,17,And God made you grow forth from the earth like plants
  71,18,Then He will cause you to return to it and bring you forth again
  71,19,And God made the earth an open expanse for you
  71,20,that you may travel spacious paths therein.’”
  71,21,"Noah said, “My Lord they disobeyed me and followed those whose wealth and children increase them in naught but loss.”"
  71,22,And they devised a mighty plot
  71,23,"saying, “Do not leave your gods; do not leave Wadd or Suwa?, or Yaguth, Ya?uq, or Nasr.”"
  71,24,Many indeed have they led astray; and it increases the wrongdoers in naught but error
  71,25,"Because of their iniquities they were drowned, then made to enter a Fire. And then they found no helpers for themselves apart from God"
  71,26,"Noah said, “My Lord, leave not a single disbeliever to dwell upon the earth"
  71,27,"Truly if you leave them, they will mislead Thy servants and will beget naught but disbelieving profligates"
  71,28,"My Lord, forgive me and my parents, whosoever enters my house as a believer, and the believing men and the believing women, and do not increase the wrongdoers in aught but ruin.”"